28 non quia tanti fuerit· - · ut: i. e. I do not'wish to be under- stood as believing for a moment that . . . simply for the sake that. The supposition is purely imaginary and merely designed to pre- vent any possible misinterpretation of Secundus' own views. Hence the subj. after ‘non quia' (z non quo or non quod, neither of which occurs in Tac.) is necessary. Cp. note c. 9 13. John ad loc., Reuss, De coniuncte. caus. ap.
